>In this question if you observe you will found out that we have given some `choices` & on that `choices` we have to make `decision`.
>>So, what choices we have given is whether **to include "Yes" or not "No".**

Let's say we have **input:** [1, 2, 3] to make it's recursive diagram. We have choices like to include 1 or not & so on...

```
       1                    2                      3
	  / \                  / \                    / \
	Yes  No              Yes  No                Yes  No
```

So, on these choices whatever decision I will take, it will make my subset!

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/e031f1ed-c20f-4999-ab43-bc49bb1e235d_1644719174.8762171.png)

So, if you see we are taking choices whether to have or not. [ 0 or 1 ] And by these choices we are making decision's. And because of that. Our Input is getting smaller.

Now let's understand, how we will build our **recursion tree**

Again, let's understand with example we have to get subset of [1, 2]

```
|  [ ]  |   1 -> 0 2 -> 0
|  1    |   1 -> 1 2 -> 0
|  2    |   1 -> 0 2 -> 1
|  12   |   1 -> 1 2 -> 1
```

So, instead of representing in `1->0 2->0` way. We want to represent in a good way & that way is called **Recursive Tree**

For Recursive tree there is a method called **"IP - OP Method"**

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/f3beda30-bb5b-4f19-8642-56ce05fff151_1644719440.842423.png)

Let's understand this tree with an example as well. **Get subset of [1, 2, 3]**

