![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/d2f21464-a034-4873-a490-179e24383fa5_1600613703.2150216.png)


For set of n elements, power set will have, 2^n elements.

so let's say.. we have elements [1,2,3]
so for every number we have a choice, we include that number, or we exclude it..

so above approach follows same concept..

Look at the image above, 
1) intially index is 0, and list is empty.. 
2) so now, element at index 0 have two functions calls, one where 1 is not included in arrayList
   and other one where 1 is included..
3) now, for level-1's dunction call, index is 1. so again element at index 2, will have those function calls..
4) continue same, till the last element. 
5) when index reaches value n (i.e, processed all elements) 
   copy the content of list into other arraylist, and insert it into new list.

NOTE: if you have noticed, all lists will be unique.. reason is, this approach creates, exactly 2^n paths from root to leaf nodes and every leaf node represents one list from power set.

Time Complexity: 
1) let's ccreate recurrence relation first.. T(n) = 2*T(n-1) &  if(n=1) T(0)= 1;
2) so now, T(n) = 2*2*T(n-2)
3) T(n) = (2^2) * T(n-2)
4) if we generalize this expression, using k,
    T(n) = (2^k) * T(n-k)
5) when k=n,
    T(n) = 2^n * T(0) and T(0) = 1;
therfore time complexity of above program is, T(n) = 2^n

