**Problem Statement:** Given an integer array nums of unique elements, return all possible subsets (the power set). The solution set must not contain duplicate subsets. Return the solution in any order.
## Approach 1: Using Optimal Substructure
**Intuition:** 
If we know all the subsets of vector of size n, so, we know the solution for nums[1..n-1]
Eg - n=3 nums[1,2,3]
`Subsets for [1, 2] => {[],[1],[2],[1,2]}`
Now, as you can see on adding one more element 3 in above set, 
* all  the subsets of nums[1..n-1] are also subsets of nums[1..n], so copy them
* in all subsets of nums[n-1] add one more element at the end and it will create the subsets resulted by adding the last element
So,
```
subsets of [1,2,3]= { [] , [1] , [2] , [1,2] } + { []+[3] , [1] + [3] , [2] + [3] , [1,2] + [3] }
                    |  subsets of [1,2]        |   new subsets due to element 3                 | 
					={ [],[1],[2],[1,2],[3],[1,3],[2,3],[1,2,3]}
```
