class Solution {
public:
    vector<vector<int>> subsets(vector<int>& nums) {
        vector<vector<int>> superset={{},{nums[0]}};
        for(int i=1;i<nums.size();i++){
           vector<vector<int>> curr=superset;
            for(auto vec : curr){
                vec.push_back(nums[i]);
                superset.push_back(vec);
            }
        }
        return superset;
    }
};
```
**Time Complexity=O(n*2^n)**
## Approach 2: Bit Manipulation
Intuition-
For set of size n, we know there are 2^n subsets.  So, each element is represented by a bit of N (=2^n)
for i=0 to 2^n-1
    select the elements from array whose bit is set
Example-
For n=3, there will be N=2^3 = 8 subsets.
representing i as 3 bits
i=0 => [000] => []
i=1 => [00**1**] => [1]
i=2 => [0**1**0] => [2]
i=3 => [0**11**] => [1,2]
i=4 => [**1**00] => [3]
i=5 => [**1**0**1**] => [1,3]
i=6 => [**11**0] => [2,3]
i=7 => [**111**] => [1,2,3]
```
