# DFS Iterative
This Solution is a simple extension of **DFS Iterative Pre-Order Traversal** 
1. Tree needs to be built. So In-Order or Post-Order cannot be used which require to visit child before visiting parent.
2. Only Pre-order (Top-Down) is possible.

***DFS Iterative Pre-Order***
1. Create nodeStack 
2. Add root to stack
3. while nodeStack not empty
	* 	Pop a node out of the stack
	* 	Visit the node
	* 	Add left child to stack
	* 	Add right child ot stack

***Extension for this problem***
* We do not have a tree yet.
* Need to build the tree
* So no point creating nodeStack
* Instead create positionStack to keep track of the position ***( nums[position] )*** we are dealing with at the moment.
* Each position in num[] array crossponds to each level in the tree
* Start with position 0
1. Create new levelStack 
2. Add position 0 to levelStack
3. Create a tempList - as a carrier to transport values from parent to child
4. while ( levelStack not empty )
	* pop() position from levelStack
	* We will be dealing with nums[positon] in THIS iteration
	* Check Exit Condition
	* Time to create left child
		* Do not add this num[position] to tempList for left child
		* Push position+1 into stack
	* Right child
		* Add nums[position] into tempList
		* Again Push position+1 into stack for right child 

	* Exit condition
		* Check if we are at the leaf
		* If yes - Then its time to record the node to result list
		* Once result is recorded restore tempList to previous state (backtracking)
```
class Solution {
    public List<List<Integer>> subsets(int[] nums) {
		if(nums == null || nums.length <= 0)
			return new ArrayList<>();

		List<List<Integer>> res = new ArrayList<>();
		Stack<Integer> levelStack = new Stack<>();
		List<Integer> tempList = new ArrayList<>();
		levelStack.push(0);

		while(!levelStack.isEmpty()){
			int pos = levelStack.pop();
			if(pos == nums.length){ //Exit condition
				listCnt++; 
				res.add(new ArrayList<>(tempList));
				if(!tempList.isEmpty())
					tempList.remove(tempList.size()-1);
				continue;
			}
			//Left child
			levelStack.push(pos+1);
			//Right child
			tempList.add(nums[pos]);
			levelStack.push(pos+1);
		}
		return res;
    }
}
```

