A binary search algorithm is used to solve the problem. We check the average value of n(mid), if it is true(bad), then we do an additional check for a false value in front of it, if so, we return our mid, otherwise we continue our search.
If our average value is false, we "reject" the half that comes before this value, and repeat the search again, already among the "new" half.

