Since we need leftmost value, we can use another binary search that is setting high to mid and return low.

Think about the case when mid is bad version, in that case the bad version started at some x <= mid, the required result will be in range [low, mid] so we set high to mid.

The terminating condition is low >= high, in that case low is first bad version since any elements below low are always good version.

