# How I think and implement it?
(1) Set the range of L, R should be `1,n`
(2) write done the condition of matched case. In this problem, we have the condition
`isBadVersion(M)  && (M-1<1 || !isBadVersion(M-1))`
(3) When tha matched case is not happened, we need to decide search right-side or left-side.
So , when the logic condition `isBadVersion(M)`  is true, then go to the left-side. 
Otherwise, go to the right-side.

So we have th following code
```C++
class Solution {
public:
    int firstBadVersion(int n) {
        int L=1,R=n;
        while(L<=R) {
            int M = L+(R-L)/2;
            if(isBadVersion(M)  && (M-1<1 || !isBadVersion(M-1)) ) {
                return M;
            }
            if(isBadVersion(M)) 
                R=M-1;
            else 
                L=M+1;
        }
        return -1; //The code will not be wrong becuase so there's no such case happened
    }
};
```

